description.narrative:
Overall Objective: to contribute in creating employment opportunities through enterprise development of women groups in rural areas.
The specific objectives for the project are:&nbsp; 
&middot; Enhanced development and growth of women groups small enterprises 
&middot; Promoted new small enterprises for women groups.&nbsp; 
The purpose of the project is to facilitate the creation of decent and productive work opportunities for young women and men through promoting environmentally friendly enterprises for women groups. This will be achieved through: organizing women at the individual and household levels into groups, facilitating entrepreneurship development for women groups to start and grow their small enterprises; enhancing access to productive assets and build their capacity to own and manage their enterprises, enhancing their access to finance; fostering their access to local and regional markets; enhancing access to business development services in the market. In addition, the project will enhance networking and partnership to support women groups through establishing communication with private companies and gender units at chambers of commerce, to benefits from existing programs and services.
The proposed project focuses on the identified rural areas in four governorates namely, (Jenin, Tubas, Jericho, and Salfit) in Palestine. The project scope of work will focus on: &nbsp;(1) strengthening existing and establishing new enterprises for women groups, (2) engaging women processing groups effectively in the value addition of the production and (3) strengthening value chains that provide improved access to affordable and better quality products in the market. 
